# Git Conventions

Shares the same conventions as the ninoprodigio platform so history and tooling
stay consistent across both repos.

## Commit Messages (Conventional Commits)

Format:

```
<type>: <description>

[optional body explaining WHY, not WHAT]
```

| Type | When to use |
|---|---|
| `feat:` | New feature or capability |
| `fix:` | Bug fix |
| `docs:` | Documentation only |
| `chore:` | Maintenance, dependencies, tooling |
| `refactor:` | Code restructure without behavior change |
| `perf:` | Performance improvement |
| `style:` | Formatting only |
| `test:` | Adding or updating tests |
| `ci:` | CI/CD configuration |
| `feat!:` / `fix!:` | Breaking change |

Rules:
- Description in English, lowercase, imperative mood ("add" not "added").
- No trailing period; first line under 72 chars.
- Body explains WHY, not WHAT.
- Use scope when useful: `feat(fulfillment):`, `fix(payment):`, `feat(minutes):`.
- NEVER use `chore:`/`docs:` for commits that include functional code — use
  `feat:`/`fix:`.

Useful scopes for this repo: `catalog`, `cart`, `payment`, `fulfillment`,
`returns`, `minutes`, `admin`, `subscriber`, `workflow`, `config`.

## Branching & Merge

- Work on feature branches: `feat/...`, `fix/...`, `docs/...`, `chore/...`.
- Never commit directly to `main`.
- Merge via PR + **squash merge**; the PR title (Conventional Commits format)
  becomes the squash commit message. Keep `main` history clean.
- Never force-push to `main`.

## Cross-repo changes

When a change spans this repo and `ninoprodigio-platform` (e.g. the
`order.placed` payload or customer mapping in `docs/integration-contract.md`),
land coordinated PRs and reference the counterpart PR in each description.

## Secrets

Never commit `.env` or any secret. Keep `.env.template` updated when adding a new
variable. Do not commit Stripe/Shippo/Resend keys.
